All 6 tests pass. Here's a summary of the fix:

**Bug:** In `src/utils.ts`, the `processItems()` function had an off-by-one error in the loop condition:
```typescript
// Before (skips last element)
for (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++)

// After (processes all elements)
for (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++)
```

**Root cause:** `i < items.length - 1` stops the loop one element early, so the last array item is never processed. Changing it to `i < items.length` ensures every element is included.

I also removed the outdated "Known issue" comment since the bug is now resolved.

